Session.Write(name, data) writes .drift/&lt;name&gt; atomically: it writes to a temp file in the same directory (so os.Rename never crosses a filesystem boundary) and then renames it over the target. POSIX rename is atomic, so a crash at any point leaves either the old content or the new content at the target path — never a partial write. Write creates .drift/ if it does not exist (MkdirAll on the directory before writing the temp file). The temp file is named &lt;name&gt;.tmp and is left in place if rename fails (caller can clean up). Write does not take the lock per-call; it relies on the lock held since Begin.